Peer's mind.

18:53.865 --> 18:57.367
♪ Married girl,
the married girl ♪

18:57.469 --> 19:00.337
♪ She wears just any kind ♪

19:00.404 --> 19:03.807
She sang it at the very top
of her range,

19:03.874 --> 19:06.076
real mountain singing.

19:06.143 --> 19:09.813
♪ Single girl, single girl ♪

19:09.881 --> 19:13.984
♪ She goes to the store
and buys ♪

19:14.052 --> 19:17.855
♪ Married girl,
the married girl ♪

19:17.922 --> 19:21.024
♪ She rocks the cradle
and cries ♪

19:21.125 --> 19:23.260
At that time, women didn't do
a lot of singing.

19:23.327 --> 19:25.696
The singing was done
mostly by men.

19:25.764 --> 19:30.200
And to record a song like
"Single Girl, Married Girl"

19:30.268 --> 19:32.302
was very unusual,

19:32.370 --> 19:35.305
because women here were,
for the most part,

19:35.373 --> 19:37.674
at home, doing the chores.

19:37.742 --> 19:40.610
They certainly were not
liberated.

19:40.712 --> 19:43.547
CHARLES WOLFE: It turns out
that A.P. was not there

19:43.615 --> 19:45.549
because he was out
trying to buy a tire

19:45.616 --> 19:48.685
so they could have a decent tire
to drive home on.

19:48.753 --> 19:52.189
And at the end of those
two sessions,

19:52.257 --> 19:56.493
they were given a check
and sent on their way.

19:56.561 --> 19:59.596
They took off back home,
and they say that afternoon

19:59.664 --> 20:04.401
A.P. was back in his garden,
working away.

20:06.837 --> 20:10.807
Time passes, and the records
are not released.

20:10.875 --> 20:13.477
FORRESTER: They had sort of
forgotten about it, I think.

20:13.545 --> 20:15.612
They'd come home
and gone back to doing

20:15.680 --> 20:18.415
what they'd always done,
children and chores.

20:18.482 --> 20:19.916
And my grandmother probably
thought

20:19.984 --> 20:22.119
that was kind of a waste
of their time.

20:22.186 --> 20:24.687
So we made it home

20:24.755 --> 20:26.689
and never thought no more
about it, you know,

20:26.757 --> 20:30.394
never dreamed about
the record business

20:30.461 --> 20:33.330
a-turnin' out what it did.

20:33.398 --> 20:36.133
CHARLES WOLFE:
Three or four months later,

20:36.201 --> 20:38.802
Mr. McClister, who ran
the music store,

20:38.870 --> 20:41.972
wheeled a Victrola out
on the streets of Bristol

20:42.040 --> 20:45.975
and started playing
The Carter Family.

20:46.043 --> 20:50.214
♪ I'm going away
to leave you, love ♪

20:50.281 --> 20:53.883
And, of course, began selling
records hand over fist.

20:53.951 --> 20:56.854
♪ But I'll return to you
some time ♪

20:56.921 --> 21:00.557
♪ If I go 10,000 miles ♪

21:00.625 --> 21:04.828
A few weeks later,
a check arrived,

21:04.896 --> 21:06.964
and it was a pretty good-sized
check.

21:07.032 --> 21:09.299
Well, at this point A.P.
didn't apparently even know

21:09.367 --> 21:11.201
the records were out.

21:11.269 --> 21:15.005
When we got the first royalty,

21:15.073 --> 21:20.143
why, the "Single Girl, Married
Girl" had sold the most,

21:20.211 --> 21:24.114
the very one that
I didn't want to sing.

21:24.215 --> 21:28.118
[ ♪♪ ]

21:33.291 --> 21:35.425
CHARLES WOLFE:
Ralph Peer said, "Look,

21:35.492 --> 21:37.861
I think you're gonna be making
a lot of records,

21:37.929 --> 21:40.764
and I think it's to your
advantage to take royalties."

21:40.832 --> 21:44.134
And it was only then
that A.P. began to realize

21:44.202 --> 21:47.938
you made some money by going out
and making records

21:48.005 --> 21:52.475
but that the real money came
from the songs.

21:52.543 --> 21:57.981
And so A.P. Carter gets an
education in the music business

21:58.049 --> 22:00.017
from the master.

22:00.084 --> 22:03.953
So Peer wants to treat
A.P. Carter

22:04.022 --> 22:06.723
as if he's his star quarterback.

22:06.790 --> 22:08.925
This guy is the money man.

22:08.993 --> 22:12.262
He's the one who's going
to keep these songs coming.

22:12.297 --> 22:15.599
And what was amazing is that
Peer was asking A.P.

22:15.666 --> 22:17.401
to show up every three
or four months

22:17.469 --> 22:19.169
with a bag full of new songs.

22:19.237 --> 22:20.637
And guess what?

22:20.705 --> 22:23.540
A.P. did it.

22:23.542 --> 22:27.977
[ ♪♪ ]

22:32.383 --> 22:37.220
♪ It takes a worried man
to sing a worried song ♪

22:37.288 --> 22:41.525
