a worried song ♪

22:41.592 --> 22:46.430
♪ I'm worried now,
but I won't be worried long ♪

22:46.498 --> 22:49.232
MAN: At this point,
A.P. was doing

22:49.300 --> 22:51.501
pretty much ethnomusicology.

22:51.569 --> 22:55.105
He was really obsessed about
collecting songs.

22:55.173 --> 22:57.574
If he heard there was
an unknown song,

22:57.642 --> 23:00.310
he'd go down and collect
that tune.

23:00.377 --> 23:03.080
MAN: He said, "I could just look
at a house and say,

23:03.147 --> 23:04.948
'You know, there's a song
up there.'"

23:05.016 --> 23:06.616
And so he would go up
to these houses,

23:06.684 --> 23:08.352
and sure enough,
there would be songs

23:08.419 --> 23:10.120
and people would sing them
for us.

23:10.187 --> 23:15.192
♪ I went across the river
and I lay down to sleep ♪

23:15.260 --> 23:19.396
♪ I went across the river and I
lay down to sleep ♪

23:19.463 --> 23:25.101
♪ When I woke up,
I had shackles on my feet ♪

23:25.169 --> 23:26.970
