27:49.166 --> 27:53.136
CLIFTON: One February he got up
and left Sara on the mountain,

27:53.204 --> 27:57.240
middle of the winter,
with no wood for the fire,

27:57.308 --> 28:00.377
no money to buy any groceries,

28:00.445 --> 28:02.846
and said, "I need to go find
some songs,"

28:02.913 --> 28:04.213
and just got up and left.

28:04.315 --> 28:06.415
And there she was
with three small children.

28:06.483 --> 28:08.551
He just didn't think about that.

28:08.619 --> 28:10.420
He had blinders on
when it came to music,

28:10.488 --> 28:12.622
and he didn't see left or right.

28:12.689 --> 28:13.923
It was music.

28:13.991 --> 28:15.859
WOMAN: And anything
that needed to be done,

28:15.926 --> 28:18.060
Sara was the one
that had to do it.

28:18.128 --> 28:22.231
And she got tired of that
after years and years

28:22.233 --> 28:23.666
and just kind of, I think,
developed

28:23.734 --> 28:27.804
a lot of resentment there that
couldn't be undone.

28:27.872 --> 28:31.541
She also didn't like the life
in the spotlight as much.

28:31.608 --> 28:34.610
She felt like she was being made
to do that.

28:34.679 --> 28:38.447
Eventually it just was
too hard for her.

28:38.515 --> 28:41.918
And A.P. had asked his cousin
Coy Bays to kind of help

28:41.986 --> 28:44.154
while he was gone
and look after things

28:44.221 --> 28:46.723
and help take her on errands,
fix things.

28:46.791 --> 28:48.858
And they spent a lot of time
together

28:48.926 --> 28:51.061
and they ended up falling
for each other,

28:51.128 --> 28:53.663
and it changed everything.

28:53.731 --> 28:55.832
Coy was A.P.'s cousin,

28:55.900 --> 28:58.534
and no one really knew
how to feel about it,

28:58.602 --> 29:03.439
so Coy's family just packed up
and moved to California.

29:03.507 --> 29:05.541
There was nothing
that was going to save

29:05.609 --> 29:07.711
A.P. and Sara's marriage
at that point.

29:07.778 --> 29:10.380
The damage had been done,
and the marriage was broken.

29:10.447 --> 29:13.049
And Sara went back home
to Copper Creek

29:13.117 --> 29:16.820
on the other side
of the mountain.

